caption: Really good atmosphere
Rosalind is as an awesome waitress! The food was fabulous, quick and hot! This is my second visit and I will definitely be back!

Visited the tavern recently. The reception left a lot to be desired in terms of hospitality. The host, a young man, who seated us seemed mildly irritated by our presence. He sat us right behind the hosts’/hostesses’ desk, where we had front row seats  of the hosts and hostesses as they went about their duties with masks partially/fully off!! Our waitress on the other hand was such a breath of fresh air!! She was friendly, attentive and ensured we were well-taken care of the entire time. The food was decent...the shrimp and chorizo dip was the best bite we had all evening. Our food was lukewarm, pretty much cold when it arrived. My Swiss Taverna burger was still pink in the center although I was not asked how I’d like it prepared, the hubby’s hotdogs were bland, cold and the cheese sauce as bland as the dogs. The fried oreos dessert we took home were delicious!! A perfect ending to a not-so-perfect meal.

We were in downtown Alpharetta looking for a place to eat and picked Central City Tavern.   We made a great choice.  Food, service and atmosphere were all fantastic.  Would highly recommend and will definitely be going back!
Bar staff awesome people were great.
Great area, great ambiance, great food.
Fun place to grab a happy hour drink in the heart of downtown Alpharetta.
Stopped in for a quick look and had brand new dark IPA fresh off the tap.  Staff was really friendly and service was great.  I'd definitely recommend for a good time.
Thanksgiving Day, hardly anyone here. Warm inside to come in and grab boneless chicken wings. They were VERY small. 6 bites of chicken for $7. Wow!

The service was ok and the atmosphere was nice but the food was just awful and extremely overpriced for something that I could barely stomach. Also, somehow I paid $9.50 for a shot of well vodka. Would not recommend if you're trying to eat or drink. Trivia was fun though

If you’re looking for a great, local spot with outstanding service in Alpharetta - Keep looking! Been here three times (months apart from each other) since its opening, and the service and attitude of staff continues to disappoint.
Best selection of food. It was so hard to decide what to get! The buffalo chicken tacos were mouth watering.
Chris and Aly (the bar tenders) were very personable and knowledgeable. Offered a few suggestions on draft beers. The street corn was great, but make sure you bring a floss stick.
Please don’t waste your money here. Horrible service horrible food and HORRIBLE MANAGEMENT!

Not only did one of the bartenders steal my car but the manager insisted on authorizing another form of payment from me without compensation. Additionally the bar is overpriced, the food is TRASH, and the ambience is unwelcoming. Please spend your valuable money elsewhere as this place does not care about service, gratitude, or quality of experience. HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE WILL NEVER RETURN!
Terrible service and terrible staff, truly do not appreciate or respect the customer

Walked over to this little gem to try something new for lunch. This is what a sports bat should be. TVs with sports programs on mounted everywhere.  Call it upscale bar food or tavern fare... I call it delicious.  Kept it simple... wings and fries and they were great. Server was attentive but not annoying.  Manager checked on my twice.  Great place and would highly recommend.
Nice bar food place.
Great place for a beer
Great place, good food, great vibe. A bit busy and loud on the weekends but hey, that's what happens to good places, they get busy and loud. Weekdays are really great, perfect to meet with friends.
Bar tenders are super nice, and the atmosphere is great to watch live sports.  One of my go to places late night.
We shared a dip that had shrimp with roasted corn it was delicious! My DIL is highly allergic to corn they were very kind and put it on the side.
Wonderful atmosphere. Friendly staff.
Great food and wonderful service! The fried green tomatoes were some of the best I have ever had.
Service was great . Server was very knowledgeable and very kind . Will definitely come back

Service was below average. They weren't busy and they seemed to have adequate staff but we had to remind them after about 15 mins.  that we had been seated.  Food was typical bar fare.  We had burgers.  They were above average. Old fashioned and the swiss mushroom.  Server probably came to our table a total of three times.  We had to flag her down for our check.  Not impressed. Probably won't be back.

Let me tell you about central city tavern. Central City Tavern welcomes discrimination and atl-right thinking. My friend shared his experience with his VALID citizenship identification, and after hearing about his experience with the manager... I will never step foot into this restaurant and I am upset that I even have to write this review, but do better City Tavern. Your business with BIPOC depends on it.
Really nice sports bar! Customer service was great! The buffalo cauliflower is the BEST I’ve ever had and I crave it all the time lol!
Great Sunday Funday spot eith friends.

Second chance for CCT months apart and the service was still very bad. When I asked the waiter what was on rotating tap he said he was new and had no idea. He didn't say "let me go ask", he excused himself to go help another table then came back with our water which he already brought us. I asked him what dark beer he had and he replied, I really am new and have no idea. I know he was new, but he could have asked someone who did know. My first experience there we sat for 15 minutes before the bartender acknowledged that we were there. I won't be back.
Food and service were GREAT! Drinks were just OK. A bit overpriced but I think I'll probably come back.
Hostess rocks! Great place to hang out with friends. Fun atmosphere.
Great place to get a beer or a cocktail and hang out with friends outdoors.
This place always delivers on the quality of food, fun, and atmosphere.  We've been here at least 5 times and all times were consistent and delicious!
Great smothered tater tots. Atmosphere is sports, energy, active - I loved it.

Who is Lexie?  She is new, ya don’t say?  Couldn’t of had a better experience. Cct has been a favorite and have only now felt the need to wright a review. Way to go!  Everyone has always been great, but boy oh boy...that Lexie is something else!!  5 million stars all the way.
Great friendly service and we'll made cocktails

First time at restaurant. Service was okay but not great. Loved the menu options but the food was average at best and the prices were too strong for the quality and flavor. Won’t rush back. Good place to watch a game and have a beer.
One of the best burgers I've had in a long time!
We tried the Carnitas tacos, it was amazing.We are going to return very soon. Thank you for great food.  Nicole, Kevin and Carolyn aka Carebear.
Cool place, but the service and beer quality was lacking.

You want some good food . Check this place out.  The staff is great and the managers there are on there game. The kitchen manager andrew is the bomb . He has that kitchen running top notch. The grouper tacos are unbelievable.  I have to try something new every time I'm there . Thanks guys for a great experience.  I'll add some photos soon .
It was unbelievably  loud - conversation  was virtually  impossible.  I found the restroom set up quite  inadequate.  There were only four individual bathrooms  for the entire  establishment.

We were very disappointed to be treated rudely by the manager. On a freezing cold night we were told to “get out and stand outside” while we were waiting in our lyft. It was a bad way to end the evening as we had a nice time at our table. We were singled out by this unhappy grumpy rotund bearded manager as there were several patrons still in the bar. We will not be coming back. If you like being disrespected this is the place for you!
Good food, itty bitty wings, tasty but far from the advertised “jumbo”
Chicken Taco Salad is the best ever !!!

Great atmosphere in the downtown Alpharetta live, work and play environment.  Can't wait to go when we can sit outside on the rooftop deck.  Food was really good; I had the swiss, mushroom burger and my boyfriend had a good ole hot dog!  If you have a craving for tater tots...this is the place!  Very hot, lightly fried and soooo good!  Danny was our server and he was about 90% of the reason we had such a good impression on our first visit.  He was so friendly and pleasant...felt like we knew him.  Wil definately be back.

Horrible service!! We were willing to wait on a table for 20 minutes as we were told. But after thirty minutes of waiting at the bar for a cocktail to enjoy while waiting we received no service. Completely ignored!!! We tried waving the bartender and or the manager down but still no service. Walked on over to The South on Main and even though there was a wait we were given great service!!
Amazing vibes, always packed out
Had the chili dogs and the lamb burger. Both were very good.  Got to sample a new appetizer during lunch today. Brussel Sprouts!!  They were amazing.
Awesome!
Food was very average - atmosphere was decent overall. Had expected this place to be good enough to compete with the neighboring bars and restaurants.

When I have visited I have always cozied up to the bar and the staff there has been excellent. More importantly, they are able to guide you through the food menu to food choices you will absolutely love. Great location. Great food. Great drinks. Great staff.   You can't go wrong with this place!

my wife and I went to CCT last night for the first time. she had grouper tacos and i had old fashioned burger with fries. Both dishes were tasty, prompt, and prepared as we asked. service was terrific (thank you Danny). I read mixed reviews but our experience couldn"t have been better.
Awesome service and staff!
Great place great Vibe

Adequate is the best way to describe this place. I have been there twice. The service is attentive but the server staff has a lot to be desired. Food was adequate and the restaurant was not what I would describe as clean. Best visited for drinks. With all of the competition in the area it will be a minute before I would return.

Great service and great food. Roasted wings are the some of the best I have ever had.  They have a shuffle board table = cool points. Great location, great place and great people. Will always be back.
Good service and atmosphere. Great beer selection. I would give it 5 stars but we didn't try the food. The 🥨 looked really good!
Great service and great atmosphere. Perfect for a chill night
Great service and the bartenders are very nice. Delicious food and good beer choices. Best tots ever!
👍 Nice place with great food selection and fun atmosphere!
The menus and the food are very good . Service is very slow and took forever . We have been there 3 times and We had the same slow service each time.
Food is so good.... Aka the wings
Very tasty pub food! Great sports bar environment!

Found this place while searching for lunch in Alpharetta City Center. We were actually heading towards Jekyll Brewing which is on the floors above CCT in the same building. Lunch was fantastic. Great menu, superb service, amd fantastic spaces both inside and outside. The CCT "signature roasted" wings were very tasty and tender. The generously portioned Asian Shrimp Salad had a nice level of spice and a complex flavor and texture profile.  Our entire dining party was impressed with the experience, and I look forward to a return visit soon. Plenty of free parking in the nearby City Center parking deck.

Excellent food and a great beer selection. Beers from upstairs (Jekyll Brewery) are on draft, also. The TVs and sound system are setup nicely to watch sports but still not be too loud for conversation.

The Central  City Tavern  is a typical "Sports Bar"  and that gets three stars It is not a "eatery" or "restaurant", It does serve the typical burgers, wings,  tacos,  greasy fries , tasteless salads  and other fast/junk food that has become the Standard American Diet (SAD). and has let to the epidemic of obesity, heart disease and diabetes and for that Central City Tavern gets Zero stars. Do not take children to eat, that would amount to neglect. The waitstaff were efficient and pleasant. So if you are a sports fan and are willing to pay high prices to get out to watch a football game and have a few drinks with friends, you will likely find Central City Tavern a good choice.
Christy is awesome !
Great pub food to!
Come here if you want to enjoy downtown Alpharetta. Kristy said this review was worth writing.
Josh was awesome!
One of my favorite places to hang out with friends for food and drinks....a special shout out to my favorite bartender Christie😘
I love this place! Great staff, always a good crowd, all around good vibe. Special shout out to bartender, Christie. She's a pro and she rocks!!
Danny could have not given any better service for us Texans!  Thanks Danny

Great dinner. We just drive in from Virginia and found it open late thanksgiving night. Danny was our server. Excellent! I had shrimp and grits bowl, hubby had the Buddha bowl. And fried Oreos for dessert. Much needed after a long trip!
JOOOOOOOSH = the man. Super helpful and attentive!
Great food and atmosphere for everyone! Our Server Josh was excellent!

Alpharetta has needed a sports bar for so long and Central City takes the cake!  Sara the bartender was super knowledgeable about the menu, and took great care of us even though the bar was slammed. Never sat for more than a couple of minutes before I got a new drink. We will definitely be back!
Was pleasantly surprised by the atmosphere and Josh’s service was great!
Josh was awesome. Food was awesome. We will be back!
Great food, beer, service, and an awesome atmosphere! Excided to go back with my friends and family!
Fun place for sure!  Kristi and Sara are amazing!!  Always have a few suggestions but overall I love it and will keep coming.

Absolutely love this place.  You are treated like family the second you walk in.  Kristy and Sara behind the bar are second to none!!  Friendly, comfortable atmosphere and truly a neighborhood place to just relax and unwind.
Very cool spot. Love the indoor/outdoor bar area and Sara was the best bartender!! 🙌🏽
Our server Josh was such a nice guy, super helpful and more than willing to answer questions and take refills. The grouper tacos were very good and tasted great.
Sara is amazing, super cool and make the best drinks!! You have got to come!!
Fun late night atmosphere and a cool place to grab a drink and hang out for trivia on Wednesday. Quick service and nice servers. Love Chelsea and Ryan.
Fun place
Great staff! Love the way they remember your name!

Awful. Went to the bar, there were 3 bartenders who ignored us for about 10 minutes. One of the bartenders even cleaned off a couple of glasses right next to us, and she decided to just go to the other side and continue ignore us. We had to ask to be served. As a newer establishment to the area, I would think they would want to make a good impression, but after going in it seems they couldn’t care less.
Fun new spot in downtown Alpharetta!

Great location in the heart of downtown Alpharetta. Perfect for an after work escape. Kuddos to the bar staff, especially Sara. One of the best I've come across, super attentive and always ready to take your next order.
The chicken taco salad is yummy and Sara the bartender is super attentive and knowledgeable about her libations! Amazing service!

Great late night bar spot. Amazing team, Chelsea, Cameron, Ryan and Sam to name a few, really know how to make everyone feel welcome. Great drink menu and quite a few vegetarian options and good barfpod options, I especially love the Buffalo cauliflower. Perfect spot to have a drink and watch a game or just hang out. The spacious bar is typically full, but never lacking good service.

Waited for waitress...waited for drinks....figured it was just because they were new and working out the kinks.  However we finally got food and had overcooked rice and funky tasting chicken.  It is a real bummer because it is a great spot.

We tried Central City Tavern for the first time today for lunch.  I liked the atmosphere and location.  Service was great.  The food was ok, but could use some improvement.  I think it is a great place to watch and game, drink beers, and snack but, not a place that I would currently recommend to visit for the main purpose of dining.  I had the Buddha Bowl, which was ok, but could use a little more spice or seasoning.  I added Tabasco sauce but still could not get it where I wanted it.  I also had the buffalo cauliflower, which tasted ok but, had too much breading.  After tasting one piece I extracted the remaining pieces of the cauliflower from the breading. I’ve had buffalo cauliflower at other restaurants where they cook it with the buffalo sauce but, without breading.  I’ll ask CCT if they can prepare it that way when I return.  My wife had the buffalo chicken bowl and she said her bowl was ok, but, had mostly potatoes.  She was happy that her chicken did not have the breading that was on my cauliflower.  I tasted some of her leftover potatoes and thought it had better flavor and spice than my Buddha Bowl.  My daughter had traditional wings without sauce and thought they tasted very good.  She also like the fries but, they had too much seasoning.  I tasted her fries and agree with her opinion.
Visited 11/13 for the Grand Opening Celebration. Food - good, service - spot on, management - confused, music/TV's - too loud.
I'm so excited about this new spot in Downtown Alpharetta! Great Food, Great Drinks & Great Service. You also can't beat the fun atmosphere. I highly recommend!

Great location and beer selection. The food is pretty good but nothing to write home about. They play the TV Audi and music WAY too loud. I could hardly hold a conversation with the two people at my table.

Central City had a rocky opening but regardless of what they showed people About themselves they are still packing in for football on Saturday. There’s a large bar with plenty of seating but too few tenders for the crowd and the bartenders will only take one order at a time and move at the minimum pace they can get away with and still be considered human. They all seem confused by the POS and it often takes two to enter and retrieve orders. They will only take one order at a time and have no system for moving down the bar. The food is mediocre at best.  It’s a shame because there’s at least one bright shining light waitress who actually gets it. Even the host can’t remember who is checked in and who is next.  Prices are meh.  Spend your money elsewhere!
username: Hutch Morrone, Your Real Estate Agent

caption: Atmosphere was good.... place has great potential. But the food was meh and didn’t encounter one employee (including our server) who had a smile on their face. Probably won’t be back.

I came in was not greeted or acknowledged. Sat at the bar for about 15 minutes still was not acknowledged. Left and was not given a goodbye. It was not busy at all on a Thursday night. Horrible service. Left and went somewhere else where I was waited on immediately upon walking into the establishment

Nice crowd, good vibe. Service was fine - not great but not horrible. For this happening location in downtown Alpharetta, I expected better food, but it was strictly *average* barfood you could get anywhere and probably pay less. The avocado in our chicken taco salads (2) was so hard we couldn’t even cut it with a fork 😬
Alexis is amazing!!! Best server ever and so much fun. Love central city tavern!

The atmosphere of this place was great.  Service, kitchen, and management need help. I don’t know if the server had too big of a section, but she was the least attentive server I have ever had. The manager was sitting on his phone at the hostess desk. The sandwiches we ordered were good, but ticket times were extremely long (for drinks too). I ordered the  steak and chorizo sandwich. The only problem was, there was no chorizo, they substituted ham, which tasted great, however it was not what I expected. We also ordered guacamole and salsa and it had zero taste and we never got the salsa. We asked for limes to fix up the bland guac... “sorry, were out”.  We notified the server that we couldn’t eat it and she apologized. 45 minutes later when she came back to the table we asked for the check.  The check still had the guac on it. We asked them to remove it, so she got the manager to take it off. Remember manager on the phone while the front of the house is going down in flames and the back of the house 86ing items unbeknownst to him or his staff?  He came over and apologized and said “yeah, the kitchen staff ran out of some stuff and just made substitutions to make it work. I apologize, we took it off the check”.  Mr manager- you should know when items are 86’d.  You should know when you servers need help.  And you should be talking to every table at least once in their visit.  Not standing there on your phone until there is a problem  Server- ask for help if you need help.  Communication is key.  If we as the customer know, we will be much more understanding.  Kitchen- make sure all staff know when something is 86’d. Don’t make random substitutions.  In this case ham for chorizo, the ham could have given someone an allergic reaction. Some people are allergic to the curing process of ham but can have other pork products.  EDIT: I stand corrected.  There is supposed to be ham in the steak and chorizo sandwich, although it lacked the chorizo the sandwich was still good. Thank you for management responding. However, please note the food was not the problem...The service and management was the problem.

Today, Sun. Afternoon went to lunch about 130. Party of 4 adults 1 child.  We waited 20 min. To be waited on and it was not that busy.  After we ordered we waited another 30 minutes for our food.  Food was good waiting NOT.

Excited to try a new spot...let’s just say I wish I could start all over and never have walked in. The food was horrible. The pretzel covered in butter was probably the most edible. My husband and daughter-in-law ordered the boneless wings, expecting tender size chicken and they were the smallest little balls I have ever seen. I’ve seen kids meals with more food than that. My southwest salad had no dressing, thank god my husband had dressing with his buffalo balls. Beer selection for a tavern is beyond weak. It is too bad. Downtown Alpharetta could have used another great dinner option! We will not be back!

Central City Tavern is new and worth a visit.  Menu is focused on burgers, tacos, and other comfort choices.  But there are a good set of options.  The vibe is engaging and energetic.  The drink options are vast with a good selection of craft beers and custom cocktails.  There is an outdoor area that melds into the main restaurant,  so you won't feel left out of the action.  Worth a return trip.  Fish tacos and chili dogs hit the spot, as did the chips and dips.

Had a wonderful experience at lunch. Josh my server was great, knew the menu and helped me pick out a drink that I would like. Then the roasted wings were the best I’ve had in a long time. Ask for a side of the jalapeño ranch with the fries!
Great food great drinks
Great! Burgers on point. Just what Alpharetta Square needed!!!
We came here for first time and it was awesome! Atmosphere is great. Food was great. The square needed a gold sports bar/tavern. We’ll be back.

Food was “okay”. Drinks were good. Service was AWFUL. Did not have GF buns as promoted on menu.  It is a great location, solid menu and I hold out optimism they’ll figure it out. We will circle back in a couple weeks to offer a second chance.

This place is absolutely amazing. I went for two soft openings and the experience is like no other. It is a perfect place to hang out with friends and meet new people. Chelsea helped me out the first time I went and she is the perfect person to talk to, not just about their food or drinks but in general. EVERY SINGLE staff member was ready to assist me when ever I needed something. It's always a stressful time starting off a new company but everyone held their composure and took care of everyone that came in. I was extremely impressed. I've been back three time since then and I'm going back tonight. Just a perfect beautiful place, amazing people and outstanding food. I can tell this is the start of a beautiful relationship lol. Now go try this place out.
OMG!!! THE CARNITA TACOS ARE AMAZING!

Went tonight for dinner. Sara was a great bartender even though they were slammed for Wednesday night trivia (which was a bonus). Wings and tots came out great and tasted amazing. Love having a sports bar walking distance to my house!  Will definitely be back!!!

Ok ok so first off I have to applaud my official Wednesday night bartenders Craig and Nicole!! They pour a mean drank!! They hold a good conversation too and immediately make you feel like a regular. The atmosphere is nice and inviting and yet intimate. The CCT Old fashioned burger is on point and I loved the Taco salad but my spin was adding salmon so it and it was delicious! Will be back as a reg6for sure!
Not opened yet, but I’m sure it’ll be great!

Horrible experience. We came to visit from Buckhead and have few drinks and the bartenders kick us out in the middle of the soccer game USA vs Jamaica. The place closed at 12am and at 1123 pm they turns off the TV in our face. Super rude from the bartenders and also is July 3rd the day before July 4th. Is nothing to do tomorrow so is no excuse why they kick us out. Bad customer service bad service. HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE
